ine 451, will be replaced with dynamic values. I'm focusing on how the current select options are built, considering the existing state variables like `selectedProject`, `selectedType`, `selectedStatus`, and `selectedStage`, to find the most elegant way to integrate the dynamic generation.\n\n\n**Refactoring Project Selection**\n\nI'm now refactoring the project selection logic within `app/portal/ai-operations/page.tsx` to handle dynamic populations of options. I'm leveraging the `agents` data to populate the options, to make it reflect accurate projects. I am removing hardcoded values around line 451. My goal is to use the `projectId` and `projectName` fields of each agent to populate the list of project options dynamically, thereby ensuring consistency and eliminating manual updates.\n\n\n"}}
